cs.SE, cs.IOT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.DS 

This paper is focused on proposing a software engineering methodology for the development of IoT systems and applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the key concepts and abstractions related to IoT systems, which makes cs.IOT (Internet of Things) another likely category. Additionally, the paper emphasizes the need for a systematic approach to the development of IoT systems, which aligns with the scope of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the state of the art in the area, which could be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
